rt integration: a multiple case study of supply chains in the UK off-trade wine market.&lt;/p>

&lt;p>The research will examine in detail a number of supply chains catering for the import of wine from Europe and beyond destined for the UK off-trade in two research channels. The first channel will examine the supply chains' performance from the perspectives of cost and risk against the background of European and other relevant directives, regulations and initiatives including, but not limited to, transport, environmental and security. &lt;/p>

&lt;p>The second research channel will seek to examine the level of supply chain integration based on Stevens (1989) model using empirical data collected from industry and to make recommendations for further integration. &lt;/p>

&lt;p>The research will follow a case study-based methodology which includes survey questionnaires and semi-structured interviews with:&lt;/p>

&lt;ul>
 

 &lt;li>wine producers&lt;/li>

 &lt;li>wine importers&lt;/li>

 &lt;li>3PLs&lt;/li>

 &lt;li>bottlers&lt;/li>

 &lt;li>distributors&lt;/li>

 &lt;li>retailers&lt;/li>

 &lt;li>other relevant parties. &lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>

&lt;p>The research will result in two academic papers for publication, based on the two research channels described in the research objective above. &lt;/p></gtr:abstractText><gtr:fund><gtr:end>2012-06-30</gtr:end><gtr:funder url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/organisation/924BE15C-91F2-4AAD-941A-3F338324B6AE"><gtr:id>924BE15C-91F2-4AAD-941A-3F338324B6AE</gtr:id><gtr:name>ESRC</gtr:name></gtr:funder><gtr:start>2010-07-01</gtr:start><gtr:type>INCOME_ACTUAL</gtr:type><gtr:valuePounds>50563</gtr:valuePounds></gtr:fund><gtr:output><gtr:artisticAndCreativeProductOutputs/><gtr:collaborationOutputs/><gtr:disseminationOutputs><gtr:disseminationOutput><gtr:description>Visit to Watermill Wines</gtr:description><gtr:form>A talk or presentation</gtr:form><gtr:geographicReach>Local</gtr:geographicReach><gtr:id>52284117-F0FD-48CE-8EC3-5223D3BCF7F8</gtr:id><gtr:impact>The purpose of the visit was to present the results of the research to the directors of Watermill Wines who were interested in the reduction in carbon footprint of importing wine to the UK in bulk versus bottled for bottling in the UK prior to sale to the off-trade.</gtr:impact><gtr:outcomeId>56ced159c31326.14499982</gtr:outcomeId><gtr:partOfOfficialScheme>false</gtr:partOfOfficialScheme><gtr:primaryAudience>Professional Practitioners</gtr:primaryAudience><gtr:year>2015</gtr:year></gtr:disseminationOutput><gtr:disseminationOutput><gtr:description>Visit to Thierry's Wine Services</gtr:description><gtr:form>A talk or presentation</gtr:form><gtr:geographicReach>International</gtr:geographicReach><gtr:id>C54F16C2-C84C-47CF-BDDB-9EC7B9194327</gtr:id><gtr:impact>The talk I gave based on the outcome of the research to the board of the company enabled them to realise that by switching from importing wine in bottles to importing wine in bulk, the company could significantly reduce their carbon footprint.

